<doc id="220466" wikidata="Q1810587" url="?curid=220466" title="U.S. list of most-wanted Iraqis">
<text>In April 2003, the United States drew up a list of most-wanted Iraqis, consisting of the 55 members of the deposed Ba&#x27;athist Iraqi regime whom they most wanted to capture. The list was turned into a set of playing cards for distribution to United States-led Coalition troops. Later, in 2003, the list was renumbered so that it mostly conformed to the order of the playing cards (see most-wanted Iraqi playing cards).

== List ==
* Total 55
* Dead: 33
* Imprisoned: 4
* Released: 14
* At large: 4

