<doc id="220481" wikidata="Q6621936" url="?curid=220481" title="List of grunge albums">
<text>This article is a list of [[grunge]] albums and EPs with articles on English Wikipedia. They appear on at least one cited album list and are described as &quot;grunge&quot; by AllMusic (). Although citations could be found describing each of these as &quot;grunge&quot;, in some cases the designation would be controversial, particularly for those bands that are considered Post-grunge.

In addition, several artists not typically associated with grunge music have released albums displaying a grunge sound, including Manic Street Preachers with &quot;Gold Against the Soul&quot; (1993), R.E.M. with &quot;Monster&quot; (1994), and Def Leppard with Slang (1996).

